\section*{Response 8: Gould and Lewontin}
\begin{enumerate}
\item \textbf {What piece of evidence in this chapter was the strongest support for descent for modification in your opinion? Explain briefly. }
\\
\par
 I think Darwin supports his claim of descent for modification best through his argument of the fossil record. Darwin says that there are various species forms within the fossil record that clearly show slow, graduated changes of a species over time. 

